records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which amends the charge to misdemeanor criminal damage to property, contrary to Section 943.01(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend twenty (20) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
2) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
3) Obtain GED or HSED;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) provide DNA sample;
7) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process.
Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence.  The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter.
Minutes.
